'''贝克德尔测验'''（{{lang-en|Bechdel test}}）是一个致力于使性别不平等引起关注的简短测验，展示了女性在电影作品中因[[性别歧视|性别歧视]]而缺乏代表的现象。该测验源自[[艾莉森·贝克德尔|艾莉森·贝克德尔]]的[[报纸连环漫画|报纸连环漫画]]《{{lang|en|{{le|Dykes to Watch Out For|Dykes to Watch Out For}}}}》。在1985年发表的一篇《{{lang|en|The Rule}}》中，一个未命名的女性角色说她只看满足以下三个条件的电影：
{| align=left cellspacing=5
|-
|
# 片中至少有两个女性角色，
# 她们互相交谈过，
# 谈话的内容与男性无关。
| 
{{lang|en|
# The movie has to have at least two women in it,
# who talk to each other,
# about something besides a man.}}<ref>Bechdel, Allison. Dykes to Watch Out For. Firebrand Books (October 1, 1986). ISBN 978-0932379177</ref>
|}
{{clear}}
该测验是一种评判电影中女性角色代表程度的简易方法，估量这些角色是否得到了充分发展。《[[衛報|衛報]]》的作者写道：“未能通过这个简单测验的热门影片数量令人惊讶。它展现了女性复杂而有趣的生活在电影业界如此缺乏代表，或是根本不存在。我们的生命中有工作，有创造性的项目，有友情，有奋斗，还有很多其他引人入胜的事情……所以，好莱坞，开始写它们吧！{{#tag:ref|原文：{{lang|en|"It is astonishing the number of popular movies that can't pass this simple test. It demonstrates how [...] women's complex and interesting lives are underrepresented or non existent in the film industry. We have jobs, creative projects, friendships and struggles among many other things that are actually interesting in our lives... so Hollywood, start writing about it!"}}|group="原文"}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theguardian.com/science/punctuated-equilibrium/2010/nov/24/2 |author=GrrlScientist |title=The Bechdel Test |publisher=The Guardian |date=2010-11-24 |accessdate=2015-06-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518160829/http://www.theguardian.com/science/punctuated-equilibrium/2010/nov/24/2 |archivedate=2015-05-18 |dead-url=no }}</ref>”

== 历史 ==
[[File:Female_and_male_characters_in_film.png|thumb]]
[[弗吉尼亚·伍尔夫|弗吉尼亚·伍尔夫]]在她1929年的文章《{{le|属于自己的房间|A Room of One's Own}}》里提及自己在当时的文学作品中观察到的现象，这一现象在日后成为贝克德尔测验关注的焦点<ref>{{cite news|title=Bechdel-Test: Frauen spielen keine Rolle|url=http://kurier.at/kultur/4506969-bechdel-test-frauen-spielen-keine-rolle.php|accessdate=2015-06-04|newspaper=Kurier|date=8 August 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120815181554/http://kurier.at/kultur/4506969-bechdel-test-frauen-spielen-keine-rolle.php|archivedate=2012-08-15}}</ref>：
{{Cquote|快速回想起那些能占满一个壮观画廊的虚构女性，我认为她们之间的关系太过简单了。……我试图从自己的阅读经历中举出一个‘两位女性是朋友’的例子。……她们有时是母亲，有时是女儿。但几乎无一例外的是，她们的身份是由和男性的关系展现的。{{#tag:ref|原文：{{lang|en|"All these relationships between women, I thought, rapidly recalling the splendid gallery of fictitious women, are too simple. [...] And I tried to remember any case in the course of my reading where two women are represented as friends. [...] They are now and then mothers and daughters. But almost without exception they are shown in their relation to men."}}|group="原文"}}<ref>{{cite web|last=Woolf|first=Virginia|title=A Room of One's Own: Chapter 5|url=http://ebooks.adelaide.edu.au/w/woolf/virginia/w91r/complete.html|work=The University of Adelaide Library|publisher=University of Adelaide Press|accessdate=2015-06-04|authorlink=Virginia Woolf|editor=Thomas, Stephen|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130121185826/http://ebooks.adelaide.edu.au/w/woolf/virginia/w91r/complete.html|archive-date=2013-01-21|dead-url=yes}}</ref>}}

一项针对电影中性别描绘的研究分析了1950年至2006年间855部商业上最成功的美国电影，发现每部影片中平均两位男性角色对应一位女性角色，这一比例长久以来一直保持稳定。而女性角色涉及性爱情节的频率相比男性角色高出一倍，她们出现在露骨性爱场景的比例随时间推移增加<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S1054139X12000699|pages=73–79|title=Trends of Sexual and Violent Content by Gender in Top-Grossing U.S. Films, 1950–2006|journal=Journal of Adolescent Health|volume=51|issue=1|accessdate=2018-04-02|doi=10.1016/j.jadohealth.2012.02.006|author=Amy Bleakley, Patrick E. Jamieson, Daniel Romer|archive-date=2018-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180615223520/https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S1054139X12000699|dead-url=no}}</ref>。根据[[吉娜·戴维斯|吉娜·戴维斯]]“媒体中的性别”机构（{{lang|en|Geena Davis Institute on Gender in Media}}）2014年的调查，全球2010年至2013年发行的120部电影中，有姓名的角色中仅有31%为女性，只有23%的影片以女性角色为主人公，女性导演仅占7%<ref>{{cite web |url=http://seejane.org/wp-content/uploads/gender-bias-without-borders-executive-summary.pdf |title=An Investigation of Female Characters in Popular Films Across 11 Countries |publisher=Geena Davis Institute on Gender in Media |last=Smith |first=Stacy |accessdate=2015-06-04 |archive-date=2015-04-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150429212513/http://seejane.org/wp-content/uploads/gender-bias-without-borders-executive-summary.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

贝克德尔将这个测验的想法归功于她的朋友莉兹·华莱士（{{lang|en|Liz Wallace}}），她日后写到自己相当确定华莱士是受到弗吉尼亚·伍尔夫的文章《属于自己的房间》的启发<ref name="New Yorker 11 April 2011">{{Cite journal |last1=Friend |first1=Tad |authorlink=Tad Friend |date=11 April 2011 |title=Funny Like a Guy: Anna Faris and Hollywood's woman problem |journal=The New Yorker |publisher=Condé Nast |page=55 |url=http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2011/04/11/110411fa_fact_friend |accessdate=2015-06-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701095828/http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2011/04/11/110411fa_fact_friend |archivedate=2014-07-01 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Bechdel|first=Alison|title=Testy|url=http://dykestowatchoutfor.com/testy|work=Dykes to Watch Out For|accessdate=2015-06-04|date=2013-11-08|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150404002314/http://dykestowatchoutfor.com/testy|archivedate=2015-04-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>。据贝克德尔说，该测验的本意是“女权主义报纸上的一点女同性恋小笑话”<ref name="San Diego City Beat 23 July 2014">{{cite news|last1=Morlan|first1=Kinsee|title=Comic-Con vs. the Bechdel Test|url=http://www.sdcitybeat.com/sandiego/article-13243-comic-con-vs-the-bechdel-test.html|accessdate=2015-06-04|work=San Diego City Beat|date=2014-06-23|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316161800/http://www.sdcitybeat.com/sandiego/article-13243-comic-con-vs-the-bechdel-test.html|archivedate=2015-03-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>，它在2010年代进入了主流评论界，被称为“女权主义评论家评判电视、电影、书籍和其它媒体的标准”<ref>{{cite book|last=Steiger|first=Kay|editor-first=James|editor-last=Lowder|title=Triumph of The Walking Dead|chapter=No Clean Slate: Unshakeable race and gender politics in ''The Walking Dead''|year=2011|publisher=BenBella Books|isbn=9781936661138|page=104|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Lz3fp1fVw90C&pg=PA104&lpg=PA104|accessdate=2014-04-20|archive-date=2014-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140617230704/http://books.google.com/books?id=Lz3fp1fVw90C&pg=PA104&lpg=PA104|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2013年，一份网络报纸称该测验成为了“几乎家喻户晓的用语，简捷地判断一部影片是否对女性友好”<ref name="The Daily Dot 18 August 2013">{{cite news|last=Romano|first=Aja|title=The Mako Mori Test: 'Pacific Rim' inspires a Bechdel Test alternative|url=http://www.dailydot.com/fandom/mako-mori-test-bechdel-pacific-rim/|accessdate=2015-06-04|newspaper=The Daily Dot|date=2013-08-18|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150428043656/http://www.dailydot.com/fandom/mako-mori-test-bechdel-pacific-rim/|archivedate=2015-04-28|dead-url=no}}</ref>。一些主流好莱坞电影（如《[[环太平洋_(电影)|环太平洋]]》）未能通过测验引起了媒体的关注<ref name="Metro 18 July 2013">{{cite news|last=McGuinness|first=Ross|title=The Bechdel test and why Hollywood is a man's, man's, man's world|url=http://metro.co.uk/2013/07/18/movie-lovers-hit-back-at-hollywood-misogyny-with-the-bechdel-test-3886103/|accessdate=2015-06-04|newspaper=Metro|date=2013-07-18|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150317020248/http://metro.co.uk/2013/07/18/movie-lovers-hit-back-at-hollywood-misogyny-with-the-bechdel-test-3886103/|archivedate=2015-03-17|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有记者指出，这一测验依旧能引发大众共鸣是因为“它明确有力地指出了流行文化中缺少的东西：不是银幕上女性的数量，而是她们故事的深度，她们关心的事物的范围{{#tag:ref|原文：{{lang|en|"it articulates something often missing in popular culture: not the number of women we see on screen, but the depth of their stories, and the range of their concerns."}}|group="原文"}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=94202522 |title=The 'Bechdel Rule,' Defining Pop-Culture Character |last=Ulaby |first=Neda |date=2008-09-02 |accessdate=2015-06-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403192958/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=94202522 |archivedate=2015-04-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>”。2013年，四家瑞典影院和斯堪的纳维亚电视频道维亚萨特（{{lang|en|Viasat Film}}）把贝克德尔测验整合进它们的评分系统，这一行动由[[瑞典电影学院|瑞典电影学院]]支持<ref name="G">{{cite news |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/nov/06/swedish-cinemas-bechdel-test-films-gender-bias |title=Swedish cinemas take aim at gender bias with Bechdel test rating |work=The Guardian |date=November 6, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518091210/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/nov/06/swedish-cinemas-bechdel-test-films-gender-bias |archivedate=2015-05-18 |accessdate=2015-06-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 通过率 ==
网站{{lang|en|bechdeltest.com}}是一个由用户编辑的数据库，包含了4500部电影，按是否通过测验来分类，用来衡量的女性角色必须有名字。截至2015年4月，网站列出的电影中有58%满足了全部三个条件，10%满足了两个，22%满足了一个，还有10%的影片一个都没满足<ref>{{cite web |title=Statistics |url=http://bechdeltest.com/statistics/ |work=bechdeltest.com |accessdate=2015-06-04 |archive-date=2016-03-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160329132437/http://bechdeltest.com/statistics |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《[[娱乐周刊|娱乐周刊]]》记者马克·哈里斯（{{lang|en|Mark Harris}}）表示，2009年[[奥斯卡最佳影片奖|奥斯卡最佳影片奖]]的提名作品中有一半难以通过测验<ref name="EW 6 August 2010">{{cite news |last=Harris |first=Mark |title=I Am Woman. Hear Me... Please! |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20408121,00.html |accessdate=2015-06-04 |newspaper=[[Entertainment_Weekly|Entertainment Weekly]] |date=2010-08-06 |archive-date=2012-04-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120422144555/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20408121,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。新闻网站{{lang|en|{{le|Vocativ|Vocativ}}}}在分析了2013年票房最高的电影后，得出结论为大约一半影片能通过测验<ref name="Vocativ 2014">{{cite news |last1= Sharma |first1= Versha |last2= Sender |first2= Hanna |title= Hollywood Movies With Strong Female Roles Make More Money |url= http://www.vocativ.com/01-2014/hollywood-movies-strong-female-roles-make-money/ |accessdate= 2 January 2014 |newspaper= Vocativ |date= 2 January 2014 |deadurl= yes |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140103011915/http://www.vocativ.com/01-2014/hollywood-movies-strong-female-roles-make-money/ |archivedate= 2014年1月3日 }}</ref>。

英国科幻小说家[[查尔斯·斯特罗斯|查尔斯·斯特罗斯]]指出，许多电影能通过测验只是因为其中的女性角色交谈的内容是婚姻和孩子（而不是条件中的男人）<ref name="Power 2009">{{cite book |last=Power |first=Nina |title=One-dimensional woman |year=2009 |publisher=Zero Books |isbn=1846942411 |pages=39 et seq. |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=u3gDWJEJblEC&pg=PA39 |accessdate=2014-04-20 |archive-date=2014-07-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701221436/http://books.google.com/books?id=u3gDWJEJblEC&pg=PA39 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。而部分和女性相关，或针对女性观众，或突出重要女性角色的作品没有通过测验。有四位女主角的美剧《[[欲望城市|欲望城市]]》没能通过测验，女主角之一在剧中自嘲道：“四个那么聪明的女人怎么除了男友就没别的话题可谈了呢？就像有银行账户的七年级学生！{{#tag:ref|原文：{{lang|en|How does it happen that four such smart women have nothing to talk about but boyfriends? It's like seventh grade with bank accounts!"}}|group="原文"}}<ref>[http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=94202522] {{Wayback|url=http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=94202522 |date=20150403192958 }} Ulaby, Neda "The 'Bechdel Rule,' Defining Pop-Culture Character". NPR. September 2, 2008.</ref>”

贝克德尔测试还被用于[[电子游戏|电子游戏]]、[[漫画|漫画]]等领域<ref>{{cite book |last=Anthropy |first=Anna |title=Rise of the videogame zinesters: How freaks, normals, amateurs, artists, dreamers, dropouts, queers, housewives, and people like you are taking back an art form |year=2012 |publisher=Seven Stories Press |isbn=9781609803735 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=nc3GRXqgPZ8C&lpg=PT7 |edition=Seven Stories Press 1st |accessdate=2014-04-20 |archive-date=2014-07-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701231617/http://books.google.com/books?id=nc3GRXqgPZ8C&lpg=PT7 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Agnello |first=Anthony John |title=Something other than a man: 15 games that pass the Bechdel Test |url=http://gameological.com/2012/07/something-other-than-a-man-15-games-that-pass-the-bechdel-test/ |accessdate=2015-06-04 |work=Gameological |date=2012-07-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120723010634/http://gameological.com/2012/07/something-other-than-a-man-15-games-that-pass-the-bechdel-test/ |archive-date=2012-07-23 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name="MTV Geek! 22 February 2012">{{cite news |last=Zalben |first=Alex |title=''Witchblade''/''Red Sonja #1'' Passes The Bechdel Test |url=http://geek-news.mtv.com/2012/02/22/witchbladered-sonja-1-passes-the-bechdel-test-advance-review/ |accessdate=2015-06-04 |newspaper=MTV Geek! |date=2012-02-22 |archive-date=2012-05-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120515212018/http://geek-news.mtv.com/2012/02/22/witchbladered-sonja-1-passes-the-bechdel-test-advance-review/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 局限和批评 ==
贝克德尔测验只能在一定程度上展现女性在虚构作品中的代表程度，一部通过测验的作品可能依旧包含[[性别歧视|性别歧视]]的内容，而具有突出女性角色的作品却可能通不过测验<ref name="ok">{{cite news |url=http://www.oudaily.com/l_and_a/arts_and_entertainment/column-bechdel-rule-still-applies-to-portrayal-of-women-in/article_d3dc6a7d-8fcb-589c-885a-649fe33db5e1.html |first=Sarah |last=Wilson |date=2012-06-28 |publisher=The Oklahoma Daily |title=Bechdel Rule still applies to portrayal of women in films |accessdate=2015-06-04 |archive-date=2014-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140822163316/http://www.oudaily.com/l_and_a/arts_and_entertainment/column-bechdel-rule-still-applies-to-portrayal-of-women-in/article_d3dc6a7d-8fcb-589c-885a-649fe33db5e1.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。作品未能通过测验的原因可能与性别偏见无关，例如它的设定背景导致女性角色的缺乏（如1981年影片《[[從海底出擊|從海底出擊]]》的故事发生在二战时的一艘潜艇里）<ref name="antipope">{{cite web|last=Stross|first=Charles|title=Bechdel's Law|url=http://www.antipope.org/charlie/blog-static/2008/07/bechdels_law.html|work=Charlie's Diary|date=2008-07-28|authorlink=Charles Stross|accessdate=2012-07-26|archive-date=2012-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120825143125/http://www.antipope.org/charlie/blog-static/2008/07/bechdels_law.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。基于上述原因，《[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]》影评人罗比·科林（{{lang|en|Robbie Collin}}）批评了该测验，说“数据储藏和清单勾画盖过了分析和欣赏”<ref>{{cite news|last=Collin|first=Robbie|title=Bechdel test is damaging to the way we think about film|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/10450463/Bechdel-test-is-damaging-to-the-way-we-think-about-film.html|accessdate=2015-06-04|newspaper=The Telegraph|date=2013-11-15|archive-date=2015-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150322190135/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/10450463/Bechdel-test-is-damaging-to-the-way-we-think-about-film.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。作者沃特·哈克尼（{{lang|en|Walt Hickey}}）指出，这个测验无法测出一部电影是否为性别平等方面的典范，通过它也无法确保剧本的质量、女性角色的深度和重要性。然而，他写道：“这是电影领域里现有的最佳性别平等测验——也许更重要的是……这是唯一一个我们拥有数据的测验。<ref>{{cite news |newspaper= FiveThirtyEight |first= Walt |last= Hickey |title= The Dollar-And-Cents Case Against Hollywood's Exclusion of Women |date= 2014-04-01 |url= http://fivethirtyeight.com/features/the-dollar-and-cents-case-against-hollywoods-exclusion-of-women/ |accessdate= 2015-06-04 |archive-date= 2014-04-08 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140408002110/http://fivethirtyeight.com/features/the-dollar-and-cents-case-against-hollywoods-exclusion-of-women/ |dead-url= no }}</ref>”

妮娜·鲍尔（{{lang|en|Nina Power}}）写道，贝克德尔测验引发了关于虚构作品是否有责任呈现女性（或其他群体）的问题，以及是否在对女性的呈现中秉承“现实主义”的问题。她也指出，现实世界是否能通过测验还不得而知，而虚构作品对现实能产生何种影响还有待思量<ref name="Power 2009" />。

== 衍生测验 ==
贝克德尔测验启发了一系列其他类似测验。美国{{lang|en|[[LGBT|LGBT]]}}媒体[[非政府组织|非政府组织]]{{lang|en|[[GLAAD|GLAAD]]}}于2013年引入了“罗素测验”（{{lang|en|Russo test}}），致力于分析电影对{{lang|en|LGBT}}群体的呈现<ref>{{cite web |title=GLAAD introduces 'Studio Responsibility Index', report on LGBT images in films released by 'Big Six' studios |url=http://www.glaad.org/releases/glaad-introduces-studio-responsibility-index-report-lgbt-images-films-released-big-six |date=2013-08-20 |publisher=GLAAD |accessdate=2015-06-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150317104130/http://www.glaad.org/releases/glaad-introduces-studio-responsibility-index-report-lgbt-images-films-released-big-six |archivedate=2015-03-17 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。{{le|芬克拜纳测验|Finkbeiner test}}帮助记者规避针对[[科学领域中的女性|科学领域中的女性]]的偏见<ref name="CJR 22 March 2013">{{cite news |last=Brainard |first=Curtis |title='The Finkbeiner Test' Seven rules to avoid gratuitous gender profiles of female scientists |url=http://www.cjr.org/the_observatory/finkbeiner_test_gender_gap_fem.php?page=all |accessdate=2015-06-04 |newspaper=Columbia Journalism Review |date=2013-03-22 |archive-date=2013-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130404081830/http://www.cjr.org/the_observatory/finkbeiner_test_gender_gap_fem.php?page=all |dead-url=no }}</ref>。森真子测验（{{lang|en|Mako Mori test}}）得名于《环太平洋》女主角名字，由影迷提出，该影片續集未通过贝克德尔测验（因為森真子在續集的前幾分鐘便死亡）<ref>{{cite web |last=Klee |first=Miles |url=http://www.dailydot.com/fandom/mako-mori-test-bechdel-pacific-rim/ |title=The Mako Mori Test: 'Pacific Rim' inspires a Bechdel Test alternative |publisher=Dailydot.com |date=2013-08-18 |accessdate=2015-06-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150428043656/http://www.dailydot.com/fandom/mako-mori-test-bechdel-pacific-rim/ |archivedate=2015-04-28 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[Node包管理器|Node包管理器]]的[[首席技术官|首席技术官]]提出将贝克德尔测验应用到软件领域，如果程序中女程序员写的一段函数调用另一女程序员写的函数，那它能通过测试<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=seldo |author=Laurie Voss |number=571453200093437952 |date=2015-02-27 |title=Does your project pass the Bechdel test? To pass, a function written by a woman dev must call a function written by another woman dev.}}</ref>。该测验在美国政府服务代理18F用其分析他们的软件后得到了媒体关注<ref>{{Citation |title=There's Now A Bechdel Test For The Tech World |url=http://thinkprogress.org/culture/2015/03/19/3635965/tech-version-bechdel-test-often-code-written-women/ |first=Lauren C. |last=Williams |date=2015-03-19 |publisher=ThinkProgress |access-date=2015-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150324175716/http://thinkprogress.org/culture/2015/03/19/3635965/tech-version-bechdel-test-often-code-written-women/ |archive-date=2015-03-24 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=A Bechdel Test for Tech? |url=http://news.dice.com/2015/03/24/a-bechdel-test-for-tech/ |first=Nick |last=Kolakowski |date=2015-03-24 |publisher=Dice.com |accessdate=2015-06-04 |archive-date=2015-04-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150428030524/http://news.dice.com/2015/03/24/a-bechdel-test-for-tech/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> 。

